channel.title: Portforward Private Ip?
channel.description:
Ok So Basically I Got A Website On How To Portforward For D-LINK - DSL -2640R And I Need The Help With The Following..
[IMG]http://i56.tinypic.com/15nqe5k.jpg[/img] 1) What Do I Change The Private IP Too? And What Do I Change The One Next To It.. I Had 2 Choices 192.168.2 Or 192.168.3...
2) Do I Change It To TCP Or UDP Or Keep All?
Im Sorry If This Is A Nubz Question But Im Port-Forwarding First Time So.. Yeah
Thank You

item.title: Portforward Private Ip?
item.dc:creator: @Mage_mad_nes Mage mad nes
item.description:
@Mage_mad_nes wrote:

First things first is this on a website like No-ip? Or is it in your settings for router such as you type “0.0.0.0” or "10.0.0.1
" Or something similar if this is in settings then i might be able to help, Go to Start > Run > Cmd. Then type “ipconfig” and press enter. You should see this:

Ip Address . . . . . . . . xx.xx.xx.xx (or xxx.xxx.x.xxx or xx.xx.xx.x)

Pretty much a chain of numbers and periods, Where it says 0.0.0.0 in your picture put what that chain is including numbers, its your “Private” ip address every computer has one, for me i would put in 10.0.0.2
